# Apex Ground Works — design system

Use for every new page, section, card, form, modal, gallery item, CTA, and component. **Nothing should look like a different website.**

## Source of truth (code)

- **Tokens and components:** `css/styles.css` — `:root` CSS variables (`--color-*`, `--radius-*`, `--shadow-*`) and existing classes (`.section`, `.card`, `.btn`, `.input`, `.textarea`, `.eyebrow`, `.form-stack`, etc.).
- **Visual baseline:** `quote.html` (Smart Quote) and `index.html` (homepage). New UI must sit beside these without palette, radius, or spacing drift.
- **Do not** parallel a second color system or one-off hex soup on new pages. Extend `:root` if a new token is truly needed.

## Brand feel

Warm, calm, residential-friendly, clean, premium but approachable, minimal, soft, trustworthy — homeowner service brand.

**Avoid:** cold / high-tech / corporate / flashy / crowded / overdesigned / SaaS / admin dashboard / generic template.

## Color (aligned to implementation)

**Backgrounds (warm light neutrals):** `--color-page` `#f7f4ee`, `--color-page-warm` `#f8f5ee`, `--color-elevated` `#fcfbf8`, `--color-elevated-soft` `#faf8f2`, `--color-card` `#fcfbf8`. Optional reserved tones for panels/maps (add as variables if used): `#f6f2ea`, `#efe8d9`, `#e6dcc9`. No cold gray, blue-tinted neutrals, or stark white-only UI.

**Text:** `--color-text-strong` `#1f1f1f`, `--color-text` `#2d2d2d` (primary body), `--color-text-secondary` `#5d584f`, `--color-text-muted` `#6d665a`, `--color-label` `#7c766a` (eyebrows / labels). Avoid harsh pure black except rare emphasis.

**Accent:** `--color-accent` `#2f6f6a`, hover `--color-accent-hover` `#265a55`. Primary buttons, key highlights, checks, active states. Do not reintroduce bright blue as a main CTA accent.

**Borders:** `--color-border` through `--color-border-warm` (`#e5dfd2` … `#d6cebf`). Darkest warm border if needed: `#cfc6b6` (prefer adding as a token if used widely). No sharp dark outlines.

## Typography

**Font:** `DM Sans` (already loaded). Tone: elegant, readable, human — not condensed, ultra-bold, or tiny.

**Headings:** Short, confident (e.g. “Project details”, “Tell us about your project”). Avoid long marketing paragraphs as titles.

**Body:** Short, breathable, useful; avoid huge text walls.

**Eyebrows:** Small uppercase, letter-spaced, muted — match `.eyebrow` (e.g. QUOTE EXPERIENCE, STEP 1, SERVICES).

## Radius, shadows, motion

- **Radius:** `--radius-card` `26px` (large cards ~24–28px), `--radius-sm` `14px` (inputs ~12px class behavior), pills/small surfaces 12–16px, **buttons:** `--radius-btn` (pill / full round).
- **Shadows:** only `--shadow-soft`, `--shadow-card`, `--shadow-hover` — warm, subtle. No harsh / neon / dramatic depth.
- **Motion:** subtle hover, light fade, gentle transitions. No bounce, spin, or startup-hero excess.

## Buttons

- **Primary:** filled `--color-accent`, white text, pill radius, clear hover (darker accent).
- **Secondary:** soft/white surface, warm border, dark text, pill.
- **Hierarchy:** one primary and one secondary per decision area; not every control primary.

## Cards, panels, forms

Warm surface, soft border, rounded corners, simple internal spacing, no nested box clutter. Forms: match Smart Quote — soft field background, warm border, comfortable padding, clear labels (see `.input`, `.textarea`, `.field`).

## Icons

Sparingly; helpful; accent color where appropriate; consistent stroke. This repo uses **simple inline SVG** today — match that weight; if adding a library later, prefer Lucide with consistent stroke.

## Layout & images

Roomy section padding (`--section-y`, `--section-x`), calm gaps, whitespace. If a section feels dense, **reduce content** before adding chrome.

Images: rounded, soft, editorial; no busy collage; lightbox okay if subtle.

## Layout nuance

Sticky header uses light **backdrop blur** on a warm translucent bar — that pattern is allowed; avoid heavy glassmorphism on cards or heroes.

## Copy tone

Clear, practical, trustworthy, homeowner-friendly, calm. No hype, startup jargon, or “AI-powered” unless factually required.

## Before shipping new UI

1. Does it sit beside Smart Quote / homepage without clashing?
2. Colors only from `:root` (or new tokens added there)?
3. Radii and spacing match existing rhythm?
4. Warm residential feel preserved?
5. CTA hierarchy obvious?
6. Anything cold, busy, or sharp? If yes, simplify.

## Do not add

Random accent colors, bright blue CTA systems, neon, glass stacks on content, ultra-sharp corners everywhere, dashboard-style dense cards, unapproved full dark sections, crowded icon rows, overbuilt galleries, generic template chrome.
